<apex:pageBlock title="Data Masking Mechansims">
<h1>Substitution Mechansim</h1><br></br><br></br>
Substitution technique masks data by replacing or substituting  the existing content of a column with the data that appears to be similar but is entirely unrelated to the real data. 
For instance, the Names can be sanitized by substituting the real names with the names from a customized list of names.
<br></br>
<br></br>
<h1>Shuffling Mechanism</h1><br></br><br></br>
Shuffling technique masks data by shuffling the existing content of a column. Instead of generating the substitution data from separate files, the data is generated from the same column that needs to be masked. The data in a column is shuffled between rows to make the data entirely unrelated to the real data. 
<br></br>
<br></br>
<h1>Encryption Mechanism</h1><br></br><br></br>
Encryption technique masks data by encrypting the existing content of a column using an Encryption algorithm along with a key. 
For instance, the Names can be encrypted by using AES256 algorithm into a binary element.
<br></br>
<br></br>
<h1>Masked-Out Mechanism</h1><br></br><br></br>
Masking out technique also known as dynamic data masking method involves Character scrambling or masking out of certain fields.It is another simplistic yet very effective method of preventing sensitive information to be viewed. 
<br></br>
<br></br>
<h1>Randomization Mechanism</h1><br></br><br></br>
Randomization technique masks data in four ways:<br></br>
1. Alphabetic Randomization <br></br>
2. Numeric Randomization<br></br>
3. AlphaNumeric Randomization  <br></br>
4. Random Date Mechanism   <br></br>
<br></br>


